4.1 ELECTRON-2 Pipeline (Content Generation)

The E2 pipeline is the most complex workflow. Here is the node-by-node
flow:

  -------- ---------------------- -------------------------------------------
  **\#**   **Node**               **What It Does**

  1        Webhook Trigger        Receives brief_id from Approval Handler

  2        Parse Brief            Extracts topic, platform, module, funnel,
                                  duration from the brief

  3        Qdrant Brand Rules     Retrieves 15 most relevant brand rules from
                                  corpfit_brand_rules (44 entries)

  4        Qdrant Banned Phrases  Retrieves all 71 banned phrases from
                                  corpfit_banned_phrases

  5        Assemble Prompt v2     Combines static core (\~1,200 words) +
                                  dynamic Qdrant rules + brief into
                                  mega-prompt. Includes dynamic CTA per
                                  funnel.

  6        Call Claude API        Sends assembled prompt to Claude Sonnet 4
                                  (claude-sonnet-4-20250514). Max 4096
                                  tokens. \~\$0.05/piece.

  7        Parse Output           Extracts 9 content sections from
                                  emoji-delimited response into structured
                                  fields

  8        Banned Phrase Check    Scans all fields against 71 banned phrases.
                                  Dual-layer safety net.

  9        QA Gate 1: Health      Claude Haiku checks for medical claims,
                                  unsafe advice. LENIENT on wellness
                                  encouragement.

  10       QA Gate 2: Brand       Claude Haiku checks platform tone, brand
                                  voice, Fun Test (platform-aware). v2
                                  deployed.

  11       QA Gate 3: Audience    Claude Haiku checks funnel/module/platform
                                  fit + 6 hard-coded deterministic checks.

  12       Format for Storage     Combines all gate results. Calculates
                                  qa_decision (APPROVED/BLOCKED), quality
                                  score, approval token.

  13       Store to content_logs  Inserts complete record into PostgreSQL
                                  (28+ columns including cost tracking)
  -------- ---------------------- -------------------------------------------

4.2 QA Gate System

Content passes through 3 sequential AI gates using Claude Haiku 4.5,
plus 6 hard-coded safety checks:

  ------------- ------------- -------------------------------------------
  **Gate**      **Model**     **Checks**

  Gate 1:       Haiku 4.5     Medical claims, guaranteed outcomes, unsafe
  Health Claims               advice, missing disclaimers. LENIENT on
                              general wellness tips. Has DO NOT FLAG safe
                              list.

  Gate 2: Brand Haiku 4.5     Platform tone match, brand voice, template
  & Tone                      completeness, Fun Test. v2: platform-aware
                              scoring (LinkedIn 3+ OK), lenient template,
                              DO NOT FAIL safe list.

  Gate 3:       Haiku 4.5     Module alignment, funnel match, platform
  Audience Fit                fit, CTA validation. PLUS 6 hard-coded
                              checks (see below).
  ------------- ------------- -------------------------------------------

4.2.1 Hard-Coded Safety Checks (Gate 3)

These run deterministically after Haiku\'s AI check and cannot be
bypassed:

  -------- ------------------------------ ------------------------------------
  **\#**   **Check**                      **Rule**

  1        CorpFit in CTA                 The brand name must appear in the
                                          call-to-action. Missing = FAIL.

  2        CorpFit in Caption             Brand name must appear in at least
                                          one caption (short or long). Missing
                                          = FAIL.

  3        No \'free\' in CTA             CorpFit is a paid app. The word
                                          \'free\' in any CTA = FAIL.

  4        B2C conversion action          B2C CTA must contain \'download\',
                                          \'follow\', or \'save this\'.
                                          Missing = FAIL.

  5        No cross-funnel CTA            B2C with \'book a demo\' = FAIL. B2B
                                          with \'download\' = FAIL.

  6        No FunFit anywhere             Old brand name \'FunFit\' in any
                                          field = FAIL.
  -------- ------------------------------ ------------------------------------

+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+
| **QA Gate Behavior on API Failure**                                   |
|                                                                       |
| If Claude Haiku is down or returns an error, the gate auto-passes the |
| content, logs the failure to error_logs, and flags it for human       |
| review. This prevents infrastructure issues from blocking the entire  |
| pipeline.                                                             |
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------+

