8\. ORBIT Publishing System

ORBIT (Outreach, Reporting, Benchmarks & Insights Tracker) is
ELECTRON-4, completing the content lifecycle from video production to
social media post.

8.1 Three Scheduling Modes

  ----------- ---------------------- ------------------------------------
  **Mode**    **Behavior**           **Best For**

  Manual      Every post requires    Launch phase. Building trust in the
              Telegram tap. Operator system.
              picks platforms.       

  Semi-Auto   Telegram preview sent. Comfortable phase. Trust with safety
              If no Hold within 30   net.
              min, auto-posts.       

  Full Auto   E3 finishes → E4 posts Mature phase. Full autonomous
              immediately.           pipeline.
              Confirmation only.     
  ----------- ---------------------- ------------------------------------

*Default mode: Manual. Change via /orbit_mode semi or /orbit_mode auto
in Telegram.*

8.2 Platform API Integration

  -------------- ------------------ ------------------ --------------------------
  **Platform**   **API**            **Status**         **Config Key**

  TikTok         Content Posting    PENDING_SETUP      tiktok_access_token
                 API v2                                

  Instagram      Facebook Graph API PENDING_SETUP      instagram_access_token +
                 (Reels)                               instagram_user_id

  LinkedIn       UGC Post API       PENDING_SETUP      linkedin_access_token +
                                                       linkedin_org_id
  -------------- ------------------ ------------------ --------------------------

All credential placeholders are in the system_config table. The ORBIT
Publisher workflow currently uses simulated API calls. Swap in real
credentials when platform developer accounts are registered.

8.3 Publishing Pipeline

1.  E3 produces video → publish_logs.status = \'ready_to_post\'

2.  E4 Scheduler detects new video, checks ORBIT mode

3.  Manual: Telegram message with 6 platform buttons sent to operator

4.  Operator taps platform button (e.g., 🚀 All Platforms)

5.  ORBIT Publisher picks up queued items, calls platform APIs

6.  Status updates: queued → publishing → published (or failed with
    retry)

7.  Telegram confirmation sent with post URL

8.  Dashboard ORBIT tab and Published tab updated

